name: ExtensionNutritionOrder_Supplement_Type
title: Cross-version Extension `R5.NutritionOrder.supplement.type` for use in FHIR R4
description: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element `NutritionOrder.supplement.type` for use in FHIR R4.
purpose:
This extension is part of the cross-version definitions generated to enable use of the
element `NutritionOrder.supplement.type` as defined in FHIR R5
in FHIR R4.

The source element is defined as:
`NutritionOrder.supplement.type` 0..1 `CodeableReference(http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/NutritionProduct)`

Across FHIR versions, the element set has been mapped as:
*  R5: `NutritionOrder.supplement.type` 0..1 `CodeableReference(http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/NutritionProduct)`
*  R4B: `NutritionOrder.supplement.type` 0..1 `CodeableConcept`
*  R4: `NutritionOrder.supplement.type` 0..1 `CodeableConcept`

Following are the generation technical comments:
Element `NutritionOrder.supplement.type` is mapped to FHIR R4 element `NutritionOrder.supplement.type` as `SourceIsBroaderThanTarget`, concept domain: `NotRelatedTo`, value domain: `NotRelatedTo`.

element.definition: The kind of nutritional supplement product required such as a high protein or pediatric clear liquid supplement.
